Photosynthetic rate adjusted using the model developed by Farquhar,von Caemmerer & Berry (1980). The model was used to scale all Aa measurements to a common intercellular CO2 partial pressure (Ci) of 300 umol mol-1 (Aa300).This approach was carried out using Eqn 1 in manuscript, assuming the in vivo maximum carboxylation activity of Rubisco per unit area (Vcmax) was limiting photosynthesis (Aa). The kinetic constants of Rubisco (Kc and Ko, the Michaelis-Menten constants for CO2 and O2, respectively, and G, the CO2 compensation point in the absence of dark respiration, Rd) were adopted from von Caemmerer et al. (1994) assuming infinite internal conductance, with their temperature dependence functions given in von Caemmerer (2000).Rd was assumed to be 0.1 of Aa for the ANBG data.These assumptions were validated from CO2 response curves measured on the eucalypt leaves (data not shown).
